title: Aug 22, 2022 - Has Judge Reinhart Flipped on Trump Raid?
description:
Darya Dugina, the daughter of a Putin ally, was assassinated in a car bombing attack in Moscow; Poso analyzes the potential geopolitical aftermath of what Russia claimed to be a contract killing. Judge Reinhart called the Trump raid unprecedented, despite the fact that he authorized the raid in the first place; Poso calls on Reinhart to unseal the entire affidavit. A federal judge, who rules on immigration issues, was arrested for human smuggling and for resisting arrest. A new report: more than 10,000 Canadians received a medically assisted death in 2021, which accounts for 3.3% of the deaths in Canada that year. 



Here’s your Daily dose of Human Events with @JackPosobiec
